name: src/position.js
Position
description: A position with x, y and facing properties.
examples:
var position = new Position(1, 2, Position.SOUTH);

position.left().facing; // 'east'
position.right().facing; // 'west'
position.forward().y; // 1

name: facing
description: The direction the position is facing. One of 'north', 'east', 'south' or 'west'.

name: forward
description: Returns a new position that is in front of this position.

name: left
description: Returns a new position at the same location with the facing rotated left.

name: report
description: Returns a with the position's x, y and facing like this: '2,1,NORTH'

name: right
description: Returns a new position at the same location with the facing rotated right.

name: src/robot.js
Robot
description: A robot that can be moved around a table.

name: position
description:
The current position of the robot. If the robot has not been placed on the
table this will be null.

name: left
description: Rotates the robot left. Ignored if the robot has not been placed on the table.

name: move
description:
Moves the robot forward if the position in front is valid. Ignored if the
robot has not been placed on the table.

name: place
description: Places the robot on the table at the position given, if the position is valid.

params.name: position
params.description: The position to attempt to place the robot at.

name: right
description: Rotates the robot right. Ignored if the robot has not been placed on the table.

name: src/simulator.js
Simulator
description:
Simulates moving a toy robot on a 5x5 table.

Note: The 0,0 coordinate is in the south-west corner.
examples:
var simulator = new Simulator();

simulator.exec('PLACE 1,2,NORTH'); // ''
simulator.exec('MOVE'); // ''
simulator.exec('REPORT'); // '1,3,NORTH'

name: exec
description: Parses the given order and gives the instruction to the robot.

return.description: Result of the order (every order except the 'report' order returns an empty string).

name: _parseOrder
description: Takes an order string and returns an order object.
examples:
simulator._parseOrder(' place 2,1,NOrTH'); // { type: 'PLACE', options: ['2', '1', 'NORTH'] }
simulator._parseOrder('MOVE'); // { type: 'MOVE', options: [] }

name: src/table.js
Table
description: A table that has a fixed width and height.

name: isValid
description:
Checks if the given position is within the bounds of the table and a valid
location to place an object.

params.name: p
params.description: The position to check. The facing information in not used.

return.description: Returns true if the position is valid.
